        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 30 at 11:17AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 1116 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Ottawa to near Marseilles to 9 miles east
of Streator to near South Streator. Movement was east northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Seneca, Kinsman, Verona, Ransom, Marseilles, Ottawa, and Morris.
</description>
        <instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. If outdoors,
consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
